      "content": "Those points far off the curve are often the result of **non-linear relationships** that the simple linear model is too rigid to capture, or they might be genuinely **outliers**—data points that are fundamentally different from the rest of the dataset. You can characterize them by examining the leverage of those points; high leverage points are those whose input features (X values) are far from the mean of the other data points. If the errors are systematic rather than random, it suggests your model is missing a crucial explanatory variable.",
